    "ailments_description": "The most common ailments you can heal with Cistus atlanticus are wound healing, due to its flavonoids and phenolic acids that accelerate the healing process and improve the tissue repair. Cistus atlanticus also exhibits anti-inflammatory properties that help reduce inflammation and alleviate symptoms associated with inflammatory conditions. Fungal infections, such as candidiasis, can be treated with the antifungal properties of Cistus atlanticus, which inhibit the growth of fungi and yeast. Additionally, Cistus atlanticus has antimicrobial effects, including antibacterial and antiviral properties, making it effective in treating skin infections and skin irritation, such as eczema and insect bites. Its antioxidant and antifungal properties also help combat oxidative stress, diarrhea, and even cancer prevention, while also providing protection against diabetes, burns, and cancer.",
