    "properties_description": "The main therapeutic properties of Cistus atlanticus are its antioxidant activity, which helps protect against oxidative stress and cell damage, attributed to the presence of flavonoids and phenolic acids. This plant also exhibits antimicrobial properties, inhibiting the growth of various microorganisms, including bacteria and fungi, due to the action of terpenoids and saponins. Moreover, Cistus atlanticus demonstrates anti-inflammatory activity, reducing inflammation and pain, through the action of sesquiterpenes and triterpenes. Its antifungal properties enable the inhibition of fungal growth, preventing the development of fungal diseases, while its antiviral properties allow it to inhibit viral replication, reducing the severity of viral infections. These bioactive compounds contribute to the medicinal properties of Cistus atlanticus, providing a range of health benefits.",
