    "preparations_description": "The main herbal preparations of Cistus atlanticus are tea, infusion, tincture, salve, and decoction. Cistus tea is traditionally used to treat coughs, respiratory issues, and skin problems. An infusion of the leaves is also used to treat digestive issues and as a calming agent. A tincture of Cistus is used to treat anxiety, insomnia, and skin conditions. Decoctions of the roots are used to treat digestive issues and decoctions of the leaves are used to treat respiratory issues.",
